{% call components.section("Usage") -%}

  <h3>Layout</h3>
  <p>Navigation is always persistent and is located at the very top of the page on all screens. In certain situations, other components can be placed above the navigation, like an Announcement banner.</p>

  <h3>Menu vs. utility</h3>
  <p>Menus feature content related to the website that the navigation is placed on, no two websites should have the same list of menus. Utilities feature content related to Red Hat as an organization, all websites should share roughly the same order of utilities.<p>


  <h3>Utility ordering</h3>
  <p>Utilities follow a certain order to maintain consistency across websites. If a website doesn’t need one of these utilities, remove or replace it, but keep the same ordering.</p>

  <h3>Custom utility slot</h3>
  <p>A different utility can be used in the custom slot, like Help or Language. Be careful of how many utilities are used so it doesn’t overload the navigation. If a custom utility requires a new icon, contact the Brand team.</p>

{%- endcall %}

